{"build_type":"library","description":"Advance function for the tail-chain delivery fiber kind (category 3). It orchestrates a strictly sequential chain of category-2 worker fibers: each worker's result becomes the input of the next. Per-fiber slots 6 (current running value) and 7 (remaining steps) hold the chain state; the root seeds them. On first entry it launches one worker child (awaiter = self) carrying the current value and parks at pc 1. When the child completes, completion routing re-readies this fiber; the resumed pass folds the child result into the current value, decrements the remaining count, and either launches the next worker or, when the chain is exhausted, places the final value into the result slot and routes it to its own awaiter. Purely cooperative: one child at a time, single-slot await, zero clone, zero eventfd.","module_name":"advance-tail-chain-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler","package_name":"advance-tail-chain-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler","function_definitions":{"advance-tail-chain-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"s","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"t","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"five","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":5},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"six","va